Commentary Text: Bumrah to Kohli, 1 run, pulled uppishly and that's brilliantly half-stopped by the man diving at short mid-wicket. Oh dear! The throw has bounced awkwardly from nowhere and smashed into Ishan Kishan's face. He's not wearing a helmet. He's in serious pain. The physio and the team-mates rush to him. He's on the ground. Hope he's alright. Hit him side of the face, just missed the right eye luckily as he turned his head. Hardik Pandya, who threw the ball, looks puzzled. Ishan Kishan walks off. Swelling near the right eye. Gets a roar from the crowd as he is up on his feet. That's a very nasty injury, but in a way, thankfully missed the eye. The ball just hit the rough patch on the side of the pitch and jumped steeply at him

Commentary Text: Krunal Pandya to Corey Anderson, out Caught by (sub)Duminy!! Anderson departs for a blob. Not a sweet IPL 2018 debut for the Kiwi all-rounder. Pandya gets two in two. Slowish and lured Anderson into a big shot. The batsmen went low and slogged, no timing whatsoever and he ended up hitting it straight to deep mid-wicket. Commentary Text: Krunal Pandya to Mandeep, wide, out Stumped!! Once bitten twice shy. No mistake whatsoever from Ishan Kishan this time. Mandeep has been hokey-pokeyed for the second time and no repreive on this occasion. Very smart from Krunal; Mandeep announced his intent of stepping out early. Krunal sees it and lasers it wide of off. Very similar to the last over, Ishan Kishan doesn't panic, grabs it cleanly and whips the bails off. RCB lose their third wicket. Mandeep st Ishan Kishan b Krunal Pandya 16(14) [4s-1]

Commentary Text: McClenaghan to de Villiers, out Caught by Hardik Pandya!! de Villiers perishes. Huge blow for RCB. Two wickets in the over and McClenaghan is turning it on here. Seemed like a certain ploy and de Villiers fell into the trap. Dug in short and there was a fielder positioned at deep mid-wicket. AB forgets, goes for the pull, doesn't bother to keep it down either. Flat and straight to Hardik, who cupped it. Straight down the gullet, didn't even had to move there. MI on top. de Villiers c Hardik Pandya b McClenaghan 1(2)
